The paper focuses on the use of Bayesian nonparametric techniques to model complex dynamics in robot contact tasks, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of machine learning techniques such as hidden Markov models and vector autoregressive models also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The integration of these models with low-level control for online decision making suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of computer vision for the snap assembly task may also suggest a focus on computer vision (cs.CV).
